Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 02:47:32 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] asusd: GPU mode auto-switch on AC/battery via supergfxd
 dbus
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds change_gpu_mode_on_power (opt-in), gpu_mode_on_ac (default Hybrid),
gpu_mode_on_battery (default Integrated) to asusd config. AsusMuxDgpu
is structurally excluded — the AutoGfxMode enum has only two variants,
so the reboot-required mode literally cannot be a config value.

New module asusd/src/supergfxd_client.rs — minimal zbus proxy to
supergfxd (org.supergfxctl.Daemon, /org/supergfxctl/Gfx, SetMode). No
dependency added on the supergfxctl crate; we hardcode the two u32
discriminants we care about (Hybrid=0, Integrated=1), verified against
supergfxctl 5.2.7's pci_device.rs GfxMode enum.

Wired into the Phase 1 sysfs power watcher. The SupergfxdClient is
built once at task-creation time and shared into the watcher via Arc.
If supergfxd isn't reachable at daemon start (not installed, dbus
policy misconfigured), one warning fires at start and the gpu-mode
branch is a runtime no-op — kbd + profile automations continue to
work normally.

Log lines fire at INFO level on successful queue (visible in journal
even without --debug). Notifications are Phase 3 GUI territory —
sending freedesktop notifications from a system-bus daemon requires
cross-bus user-session lookup that's too much complexity for a base
patch, and asusctl-gui will run in the user session anyway.

Session UX is inherited from supergfxd's SetMode: mode change queued,
logout to apply (Phase 0 verified session-safe on FA507NV). Cancel
via `supergfxctl -m <current-mode>` before logout.

Also propagates the new fields through both migration From impls
(Config611 -> Config, Config601 -> Config).
